urls.title: Veterans Community Project
urls.description: Veterans Community Project is on a mission to end Veteran homelessness across the country. Founded by a group of combat Veterans in Kansas City, MO, VCP’s community-based solution includes a tiny house village with on-site, wrap-around services. With the peace and security of their own homes, Veterans work closely with case managers to overcome challenges related to health, employment, housing, and social isolation. The ultimate goal: permanent housing and the skills to ensure a better future. Since launching in 2017, Veterans Community Project has served over 4,500 homeless and at-risk Veterans. The project includes a village of 49 tiny houses, a walk-in Veterans Outreach Center to assist any Veteran with emergency resources, and an innovative case management model. To date, nearly 1,000 cities have contacted VCP about replicating the model in their communities. We are answering the call.
